  27,48,"And there were in the city nine men (from the sons of their chiefs), who made mischief in the land, and would not reform."
  28,19,"Then when he decided to seize the man who was an enemy to both of them, the man said: "
  28,20,"And there came a man running, from the farthest end of the city. He said: "
  28,21,"So he escaped from there, looking about in a state of fear. He said: "